{
  "Calculating pH and pOH using Log": "",
  "This lesson covers the fundamental measures of center used to analyze and summarize data sets. You'll learn how to calculate and apply the mean, median, and mode, and understand when each is most appropriate.": "",
  "If [HвҒә] = 1Г—10вҒ»вҒё M, what is the pH?": "",
  "pH = вҲ’log(10вҒ»вҒё) = 8.": "",
  "A solution has pH = 4. What is [HвҒә]?": "",
  "[HвҒә] = 10вҒ»бө–бҙҙ = 10вҒ»вҒҙ M.": "",
  "What is the pOH of a solution where [OHвҒ»] = 1Г—10вҒ»ВІ M?": "",
  "pOH = вҲ’log[OHвҒ»] = вҲ’log(10вҒ»ВІ) = 2.": "",
  "For the calculation in the previous question, what is the pH?": "",
  "pH = вҲ’log(2Г—10вҒ»Ві) = вҲ’(log 2 + log 10вҒ»Ві) = вҲ’(0.301 вҲ’ 3) = 2.699 вүҲ 2.70.": "",
  "A solution has [OHвҒ»] = 2Г—10вҒ»Ві M. What is the pH?": "",
  "pOH = вҲ’log(2Г—10вҒ»Ві) = 2.70; pH = 14 вҲ’ 2.70 = 11.30.": "",
  "If Ka = 1.8Г—10вҒ»вҒө, what is pKa?": "",
  "pKa = вҲ’log(1.8Г—10вҒ»вҒө) = вҲ’(log 1.8 + log 10вҒ»вҒө) = вҲ’(0.26 вҲ’ 5) = 4.74.": "",
  "A solution has pH = 3.5. What is [HвҒә]?": "",
  "[HвҒә] = 10вҒ»ВіВ·вҒө = 10вҒ»ВіВ·вҒө = 10вҒ°В·вҒө Г— 10вҒ»вҒҙ = 3.16 Г— 10вҒ»вҒҙ M.": ""
}